d out of Attica, with or without the supervision of their composers. This book offers a holistic examination of ancient reperformances of tragedy, enhancing our perception of them as a vital theatrical practice that played a major part in the development of the tragic genre in the fifth and fourth centuries BC.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Mrz 2018) 0aGreek drama (Tragedy)xHistory and criticism. 0aTheaterzGreecexHistory and criticism. 4aAltertum. 4aAncient Actors. 4aGreek Tragedy. 4aGriechisches Drama. 4aReperformance. 4aReperformances. 4aTragic Vases.0 cEPUBz978-3-11-055993-40 cprintz978311055986640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110561166423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110561166.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG